{{Main|:Category:Wikipedia naming conventions proposals|Wikipedia:Policies and guidelines}}

Proposals for new naming conventions and guidelines should be advertised on [[Wikipedia talk:Article titles|this page's talk page]], at [[WP:Requests for comment|requests for comment]], the [[WP:Village pump|Village Pump]], and any related pages. If a strong [[Wikipedia:Consensus|consensus]] has formed, the proposal is adopted and is added to the [[:Category:Wikipedia naming conventions|naming conventions category]].

New naming conventions for specific categories of articles often arise from [[Wikipedia:WikiProject|WikiProjects]]. For a manually updated list of current and former proposals, see [[WP:Proposed naming conventions and guidelines|Proposed naming conventions and guidelines]].

{{Short description|Article inclusion criteria for Wikipedia}}
